            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "`source()` calls `M.read(path)` unconditionally. If the caller accidentally passes a directory, `M.read()` will prompt to trust/deny the directory and may update the trust DB, but `source()` will then silently no-op (because `content` is boolean). Consider rejecting directories up-front (resolve to fullpath and check isdirectory) so `source()` only triggers trust prompts for actual files.",
            "commit_id": "ec6befcd92ee783a1e9a2761e5f53364114effbc",
            "created_at": "2026-04-05T08:33:03Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -159,6 +159,32 @@ function M.read(path)\n   return contents\n end\n \n+--- Attempt to read {path}, trusting it if necessary, and compile and execute the result.\n+--- Semantically equivalent to `vim.secure.read()`, `load()`, and `pcall()`, with proper error\n+--- reporting and chunk naming.\n+---\n+---@since 13\n+---@see |vim.secure.read()|\n+---\n+---@param path (string) Path to a file to read and evaluate.\n+function M.source(path)\n+  local content = M.read(path)\n+  if type(content) ~= 'string' then\n+    return\n+  end",
