            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "`pcall(chunk)` can return a non-string error object (Lua permits `error({ ... })`, numbers, etc.). Passing that directly to `vim.notify()` can itself error because `vim.notify()` expects a string. Consider wrapping both `err`/`run_err` with `tostring()` before notifying.\n```suggestion\n    vim.notify(tostring(err), vim.log.levels.ERROR)\n    return\n  end\n\n  local ok, run_err = pcall(chunk)\n  if not ok then\n    vim.notify(tostring(run_err), vim.log.levels.ERROR)\n```",
            "commit_id": "b2b92a6be800f9ef67c8706b8ec137a6b1a14c65",
            "created_at": "2026-04-05T08:33:04Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -159,6 +159,32 @@ function M.read(path)\n   return contents\n end\n \n+--- Attempt to read {path}, trusting it if necessary, and compile and execute the result.\n+--- Semantically equivalent to `vim.secure.read()`, `load()`, and `pcall()`, with proper error\n+--- reporting and chunk naming.\n+---\n+---@since 13\n+---@see |vim.secure.read()|\n+---\n+---@param path (string) Path to a file to read and evaluate.\n+function M.source(path)\n+  local content = M.read(path)\n+  if type(content) ~= 'string' then\n+    return\n+  end\n+\n+  local chunk, err = load(content, '@' .. path)\n+  if not chunk then\n+    vim.notify(err, vim.log.levels.ERROR)\n+    return\n+  end\n+\n+  local ok, run_err = pcall(chunk)\n+  if not ok then\n+    vim.notify(run_err, vim.log.levels.ERROR)",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38781#discussion_r3036588249",
